snippet.textDisplay: your switch should be on the ground side. its a safety hazard to have any switch connected to power because in the event its shorted the control will be HOT and you could potentially hurt yourself or damage circuitry. The switch should be in a configuration that is safe to touch ALL the time. They just do it that way based on convention... in reality ground side switching is safer.... if it wasn't then computers would control the power side too... but they don't... computers are always ground side switched for the same reason.
